In [CR-FE-4402|https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/cru/CR-FE-4402] a change was made to remove the hashtag evidence of a link being clicked. It was done as a side-effect of [CRUC-4613|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CRUC-4613]

{quote}
// clear the hash, otherwise the URL keeps the hash of the first frx we perma-linked to, even when
// we navigate away via javascript.
{quote}

This renders the permalinks nearly useless.

Instead, rather than clearing the hashtag, ensure that all "links" - either within, or deep-linking within - have a positive effect on the hashtag. This would include permalinks, urls, and navigation column URLs i.e. from the "tree".

!http://img.skitch.com/20101129-e8sjxs22yujs6t65uxa29dbhsp.jpg!

Following on from [CRUC-4982|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CRUC-4982] Seb identified that 

{quote}There is no ghost on the crucible dashboard: http://yebisu.sydney.atlassian.com:6060/foo/cru/{quote}

and 

{quote}Similarly, there is no ghost border on the fisheye dashboard: http://yebisu.sydney.atlassian.com:6060/foo/{quote}

Guess he'd like them added!
